# 🎓 AI-Based Student Performance Predictor

## 📌 Project Overview

This project is an AI-powered web application that predicts whether a student is likely to **Pass or Fail** based on key academic factors such as attendance, study hours, and assignment completion. It also provides **personalized suggestions** to help students improve their performance.

The application is built using **machine learning** and deployed as an interactive web app.

---

## 🎯 Objectives

* Predict student performance using AI/ML
* Provide actionable suggestions for improvement
* Create an interactive and visually appealing UI
* Deploy the application online for real-time usage

---

## 🧠 Technologies Used

### Programming Language

* Python

### Libraries & Frameworks

* Pandas – data handling
* NumPy – numerical operations
* Scikit-learn – ML model (Random Forest)
* Matplotlib – data visualization
* Streamlit – UI and deployment

### Tools

* Visual Studio Code – development
* GitHub – version control
* Streamlit Community Cloud – hosting

---

## 📂 Project Structure

```
AI-Student-Predictor/
│
├── app.py              # Main application file
├── students.csv        # Dataset
├── requirements.txt    # Required libraries
└── README.md           # Project documentation
```

---

## 📊 Dataset Description

The dataset (`students.csv`) contains the following columns:

| Column Name | Description                     |
| ----------- | ------------------------------- |
| attendance  | Percentage of classes attended  |
| study_hours | Hours studied per day           |
| assignments | Number of assignments completed |
| result      | Output (Pass / Fail)            |

Example:

```
attendance,study_hours,assignments,result
85,3,6,Pass
60,1,2,Fail
90,4,7,Pass
```

---

## ⚙️ Step-by-Step Implementation

### 1️⃣ Project Setup

* Created project folder in VS Code
* Set up virtual environment
* Installed required libraries

```
pip install streamlit pandas scikit-learn matplotlib numpy
```

---

### 2️⃣ Data Preparation

* Created a CSV dataset with realistic student data
* Ensured balanced data (Pass & Fail cases)
* Cleaned and formatted data

---

### 3️⃣ Model Building

* Used **Random Forest Classifier** from Scikit-learn
* Split data into training and testing sets
* Trained the model to predict outcomes

---

### 4️⃣ Application Development

* Built UI using Streamlit
* Added:

  * Sidebar inputs (sliders)
  * Prediction button
  * Result display (Pass/Fail)
  * Performance score
  * Suggestions system

---

### 5️⃣ UI Enhancements

* Added modern styling using CSS
* Implemented:

  * Dark mode toggle 🌙
  * Tabs (Prediction, Analytics, Suggestions)
  * Charts and graphs 📊
  * Progress bar for performance score

---

### 6️⃣ Running the App Locally

```
streamlit run app.py
```

Then open:

```
http://localhost:8501
```

---

### 7️⃣ Deployment (Making it Live)

Steps:

1. Upload project to GitHub
2. Connect repository to Streamlit Cloud
3. Deploy the app

Live URL:

```
https://student-perfomance-tracker-and-suggestions-kyyuhwjwzms3kbmywku.streamlit.app/
```

